docs.text: total recall is a typical sci-fi film wrapped around an intresting ( if far fetched ) plot .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: quaid , who has never been to mars , keeps on having dreams of the planet , which has now been colanised .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: one day , while riding on a train , he's see's a ad for a company called 'rekall' , which implants memories of a holiday , instead of you actually going there yourself .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: quaid chooses the 'secret agent on mars' memory , and then the s * * * really hits the fan .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the implant goes wrong , and quaid really thinks he is an agent on mars for about two minutes , until he goes back to normal and can't remember a thing .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , everyone he knows ( his workmates , his wife ) turn against him , saying how 'blabbed about mars' and 'blew his cover on the mission' a strange man , called richter , played by ironside , wants to kill him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: quaid , now hopelessly confused , follows the advice given to him , by a 'friend' .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he get's his ass to mars .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: mars is ruled by cohagen , played by cox , who charges people for air .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: against him are the rebels , who are mainly mutants .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the rebel's need quaid to defeat cohagen , because quaid knows ( but can't remember yet ) about a reactor that produces air .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: eventually , quaid kills cohagen , turns on the reactor , saves the planet , and goes away with a beautiful girl , just like the guy at rekall promised him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: throughout this plot , there is huge explosions , thousands of deaths ( and i mean a lot of death ) swearing , sex , and everything else that make's a good verhoeven ( director of basic instinct and starship troopers ) movie .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: naturally , there's some pretty imaginative deaths , with arms getting ripped off , someone getting drilled , and heads exploding .

docs.text: as you can tell , it's violent stuff .

docs.text: but it's done so stylishly , and of course arnie tones it down with a one liner , that's it excusable .

docs.text: the supporting cast are fine , and not even the comedy sidekick ( this time in the form of a taxi driver ) is annoying .

docs.text: one disappointing aspect , though , are the special effects .

docs.text: another irritating thing is the product placement .

docs.text: there are a lot of plugs ( and a good mars today gag ) however , the sets look great , and the special effects at the end of the film aren't too bad either .

docs.text: overall , then , total recall is a hugely violent , yet hugely enjoyable , action fest , with a reasonable plot thrown in there too , some great bad guys , and some imaganitive death .
